.SH NAME
polyglot\-knowledge \- curated engineering and security guidance
.SH PURPOSE
This page provides a compact baseline of engineering judgment for humans
and agents working inside the container.
.PP
It adapts durable ideas from strong software engineering and security
sources into practical guidance for this environment.
.SH WHEN TO USE
Read this page when a task requires judgment rather than just mechanics.
.SH GUIDANCE
.SS Principle: verify through the real workflow
Why it matters:
.PP
Changes are only trustworthy when they pass through the same workflow
the environment expects.
.PP
How it applies here:
.IP \(bu 2
use the container
.IP \(bu 2
use the task contract
.IP \(bu 2
treat \f[CR]task ci\f[R] as the default proof bar
.PP
Failure mode:
.IP \(bu 2
code appears correct in an ad hoc run but fails in the validated
workflow
.PP
Recommended behavior:
.IP \(bu 2
verify with the real task path before declaring success
.SS Principle: keep the source of truth explicit
Why it matters:
.PP
Ambiguous state leads to fragile automation and risky edits.
.PP
How it applies here:
.IP \(bu 2
Python uses \f[CR]pyproject.toml\f[R] plus \f[CR]uv.lock\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
dependency artifacts live under \f[CR].artifacts/scans/\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
runtime docs should explain the supported workflow locally
.PP
Failure mode:
.IP \(bu 2
